Document: HTML5 Shell Class Reference
Path: godot/tutorials/platform/web/html5_shell_classref.rst
Summary: Provides an overview of the JavaScript Engine class available in web exports for controlling the Godot engine's startup process.
Projects exported for the Web expose the Engine class to the JavaScript environment, which allows fine control over the engine's start-up process. This API is built in an asynchronous manner and requires basic understanding of Promises.
---CHUNK---
Document: Engine
Path: godot/tutorials/platform/web/html5_shell_classref.rst
Summary: Describes the Engine class for loading and starting exported projects on the Web.
The Engine class provides methods for loading and starting exported projects on the Web. For default export settings, this is already part of the exported HTML page. To understand practical use of the Engine class, see Custom HTML page for Web export.
