Document: HTML5 Shell Classref
Path: godot/tutorials/platform/web/html5_shell_classref.rst
Summary: This section details static methods available in the HTML5 shell for loading, unloading, and checking WebGL availability.

Method: load(basePath) → Promise
Loads the engine. basePath is the path to the engine's data directory. Returns a Promise that resolves when the engine is loaded.

Method: unload() → void
Unloads the engine.

Method: isWebGLAvailable(majorVersion=1) → boolean
Checks if WebGL is available. majorVersion specifies the minimum required major version (defaults to 1).
---CHUNK---
Document: HTML5 Shell Class Reference
Path: godot/tutorials/platform/web/html5_shell_classref.rst
Summary: This section details the static and instance methods available for the JavaScript Engine class used in Godot's HTML5 exports.

Static Methods
Method: load(basePath) → Promise
   Load the engine from the specified base path.
Method: unload()
   Unload the engine to free memory. This method will be called automatically depending on the configuration. See unloadAfterInit.
Method: isWebGLAvailable(majorVersion=1) → boolean
   Check whether WebGL is available. Optionally, specify a particular version of WebGL to check for.

Instance Methods
Method: init(basePath) → Promise
   Initialize the engine instance. Optionally, pass the base path to the engine to load it, if it hasn't been loaded yet. See Engine.load.
Method: preloadFile(file, path) → Promise
   Load a file so it is available in the instance's file system once it runs. Must be called before starting the instance. If not provided, the path is derived from the URL of the loaded file.
   file: The file to preload. If a string the file will be loaded from that path. If an ArrayBuffer or a view on one, the buffer will used as the content of the file.
   path: Path by which the file will be accessible. Required, if file is not a string.
Method: start(override) → Promise
   Start the engine instance using the given override configuration (if any). startGame can be used in typical cases instead. This will initialize the instance if it is not initialized. For manual initialization, see init. The engine must be loaded beforehand. Fails if a canvas cannot be found on the page, or not specified in the configuration.
   override: An optional configuration override.
Method: startGame(override) → Promise
   Start the game instance using the given configuration override (if any). This will initialize the instance if it is not initialized. For manual initialization, see init. This will load the engine if it is not loaded, and preload the main pck. This method expects the initial config (or the override) to have both the executable and mainPack properties set (normally done by the editor during export).
   override: An optional configuration override.
Method: copyToFS(path, buffer)
   Create a file at the specified path with the passed as buffer in the instance's file system.
   path: The location where the file will be created.
   buffer: The content of the file.
Method: requestQuit()
   Request that the current instance quit. This is akin the user pressing the close button in the window manager, and will have no effect if the engine has crashed, or is stuck in a loop.
---CHUNK---
